{title: Cora Is Gone}
{artist: Flatt and Scruggs}
{composer: Written by Odell McLeod}

[C]The wind through the night is blowing so lonesome
Singing to me a [G7]song
[C]A whippoorwill call is just a reminder
Pretty girls have [G7]hearts made of [C]stone
I'll [F]wake with the blues at [C]dawn
My [F]darling Cora is [C]gone
I don't know why she told me goodbye
But my darling [G7]Cora is [C]gone
The ring that she wears I bought for her finger
Purchased her raiment so [G7]fine
[C]Gave her my last green back dollar
